snippet.textDisplay:
The people in America who were whining about how our covid mitigation efforts was tyranny really look like morons when ACTUAL tyranny happens in China. 

No one is physically forced to get tested in America. No one is literally locked in their homes, and people aren’t practically ignored and left to starve when America locked down. 

Not saying the policies here were harmless and insignificant, but there’s a massive difference between practicing health safety efforts from government by mostly using local state and municipalities, and the state outright banning people from getting food to survive, with no real preparation. 

We should consider ourselves lucky we’re not in an actual authoritarian state, because if we were, we’d be doing what China has done
